{
  "stem": "19550.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To define the relationship of the Jews and non-Jews in, in Hungary is not an easy task.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You would have to have a complete sociological, political, and historical exposition.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You have to understand that although in the eyes of the non-Jews, the Jews were Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Still, there were very substantial differences in the relationship between Jews and non-Jews dependent on the history of the area and the nature of the Jewish and non-Jewish communities in, in the given area and era.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I come from Kisvarda, which is-- was in the very northeast of the country, [INAUDIBLE], what then was the Czech border and later on became the Russian border and the Polish border.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Jewish community of, of, of Kisvarda was, by and large, I would say, at least one third, if not more, relatively new, recent immigrants from the east.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were particularly the Hasidic element who were stranger than the, so to say, native Jews, who were there and belonged to the Jewish community before the days of Franz Joseph and, and what they called the 'dual monarchy.' [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so that is on the Jewish side so to say on the non-Jewish side you have to realize that in the area where I had lived I would say that the non-Jewish population was overwhelmingly what they called Roman Catholic.",
      "word_count": 84
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were some Eastern Catholics, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But-- and, and there were some reformed churches, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the overwhelming majority of the population was-- non-Jewish population was Roman Catholic, very fundamentalist kind of Catholicism, in a very real sense, quite primitive, too.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Their clergy was almost primitive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and then, at a time-- in-- even in my days, I would say that illiteracy was probably around 60%.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
